title: Ford to use Renault technology, plants for cheaper European EVs to fend off Chinese rivals
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': 'en', 'base': 'https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/auto/rssfeeds/13359412.cms', 'value': 'Ford to use Renault technology, plants for cheaper European EVs to fend off Chinese rivals'}
summary: Renault and Ford have formed a major partnership to jointly develop small, low-cost electric vehicles and commercial vans for the European market, aiming to cut costs and counter growing competition from Chinese automakers. The first jointly developed small EV—built at a Renault plant in northern France—is expected to hit European showrooms in 2028, filling a key gap in Ford’s lineup.

title: Motown hits a bump on slowing two-wheeler sales
title_detail: {'type': 'text/plain', 'language': 'en', 'base': 'https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/auto/rssfeeds/13359412.cms', 'value': 'Motown hits a bump on slowing two-wheeler sales'}
summary: Scooters and bikes account for three-fourths of all vehicles sold in the country. Last month, a decline in sales in the segment pulled the overall industry's growth down to 2% despite robust performances by cars (20%), commercial vehicles (20%) and tractors (57%).
